   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>This book is a translation of messages given in Chinese by Brother Witness Lee in Anaheim, California on February 15-16, 1992.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>These messages were not reviewed by the speaker.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>CHAPTER ONE THE ECONOMY OF GOD AND</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>THE LAW OF GOD IN HIS ECONOMY Scripture Reading: Eph 1:10; 3:9; 1 Tim 1:4b; Gen 1:26-27; 2:9; Eph 1:23; John 15:5a; Eph 5:31-32; Gen 2:18b; Phil 1:20-21; Rom 5:12, 19a, 20a; Exo 32:15; Psa 78:5; Exo 20:3-17; Gal 3:21; Rom 8:3a; 3:20b; 5:20a; Gal 3:23-24 OUTLINE The economy of God Eph 1:10; 3:9; 1 Tim 1:4b: To have man as His organism: Having His image Gen 1:27.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Taking Him as life Gen 2:9.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Expressing Him.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Representing Him Gen 1:26.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To be the Body of Christ Eph 1:23: Being united and mingled with Christ John 15:5a: Having the same life and nature as Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Becoming one with Christ Eph 5:31-32.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>As Christ s counterpart cf.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Gen 2:18b: Living Christ Phil 1:21.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Expressing Christ the processed Triune God Phil 1:20.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The fall of man: From God into sin Rom 5:12.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Man having been constituted a sinner in nature Rom 5:19a.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The law of God in His economy Rom 5:20a: The law of God being a portrait and testimony of God Exo 32:15; Psa 78:5.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>God considering His law as His requirement upon sinners: The first three commandments requiring man to have only God and not have any idols aside from God Exo 20:3-7.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The fourth commandment requiring man to take only God and all that God has accomplished for man as man s satisfaction and rest Exo 20:8-11.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The fifth commandment requiring man to honor his parents and trace back to his source, his origin the God who created man Exo 20:12.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The sixth through the tenth commandments requiring man to live out the virtues that express God according to God s attributes Exo 20:13-17.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>It being impossible for sinners to fulfill the requirements of God s law: The law of God not being able to give life Gal 3:21.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>There being something that the law of God could not do in that it was weak through the flesh of sinners Rom 8:3a.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The law of God being able only to expose man s sinful nature and wicked deeds Rom 3:20b; 5:20a.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The law of God becoming the custodian and child-conductor of God s chosen people to bring them to Christ grace Gal 3:23-24.</S>
   </TEXT>
